      <section eId="sec_20_8_2">
        <num>20-8-2</num>
        <content>
          <p>On the campus of an educational facility, a campus policeman employed by such educational facility who is certified in accordance with Code Section 20-8-3 and when authorized by the governing body or authority of such educational facility shall have the same law enforcement powers, including the power of arrest, as a law enforcement officer of the local government with police jurisdiction over such campus.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1977, p. 1160, ยง 2; Ga. L. 1979, p. 1323, ยง 1.)</p>
